a3Pattern.create_call_context:
A3 create context (nv-tb-egpu-recover.c:830-841) — runs near the END of tb_egpu_recover_init, AFTER state allocation + INIT_WORK + atomic_set inits, AFTER nvl->recover = st has been published:
```
    nvl->recover = st;

    /* Publish sysfs surface. Failure is non-fatal — recovery still
     * runs, just without userspace-visible counters. */
    if (nvl->pci_dev)
    {
        int rc = sysfs_create_group(&nvl->pci_dev->dev.kobj,
                                    &tb_egpu_recover_attr_group);
        if (rc != 0)
            NV_DEV_PRINTF(NV_DBG_INFO, nv,
                "tb_egpu recover: sysfs_create_group failed: %d\n", rc);
    }
```
The NVreg_TbEgpuRecoverEnable=0 short-circuit at recover.c:803-810 means a disabled feature never creates the group at all (nvl->recover stays NULL and the function returns 0 before reaching the create call). tb_egpu_recover_init is called from nv_pci_probe — see lifecycle_ordering.

QWD create context (nv-tb-egpu-qwd.c:406-419) — runs after kthread_run succeeded and nvl->qwd has been published:
```
    nvl->qwd = qwd;

    /*
     * Publish sysfs surface. Failure is non-fatal — kthread still runs,
     * just without userspace-visible counters.
     */
    if (nvl->pci_dev)
    {
        int rc = sysfs_create_group(&nvl->pci_dev->dev.kobj,
                                    &tb_egpu_qwd_attr_group);
        if (rc != 0)
            NV_DEV_PRINTF(NV_DBG_INFO, nv,
                "tb_egpu: qwd sysfs_create_group failed: %d\n", rc);
    }
```
QWD also short-circuits on NVreg_TbEgpuQwdEnable=0 at qwd.c:371-378 (nvl->qwd stays NULL, returns 0 before create).

a3Pattern.remove_call_signature:
A3 (nv-tb-egpu-recover.c:862-866):
```
/* Remove sysfs surface before tearing down state. */
if (nvl->pci_dev)
{
    sysfs_remove_group(&nvl->pci_dev->dev.kobj,
                       &tb_egpu_recover_attr_group);
}
```

QWD (nv-tb-egpu-qwd.c:432-436):
```
/* Remove sysfs surface before kthread teardown. */
if (nvl->pci_dev)
{
    sysfs_remove_group(&nvl->pci_dev->dev.kobj,
                       &tb_egpu_qwd_attr_group);
}
```
Both return void (sysfs_remove_group has no return checked). Both are unconditional with respect to the per-feature enable flag — sysfs_remove_group on a group that was never created is benign (no-op).

